# Englische Grammatik

Simple Present: Verwendung => Gewohnheiten, allgemeine Wahrheiten
Simple Past: Bildung => Verb + -ed (regelmäßig)
Present Perfect: Bildung => have/has + Past Participle

Unterschied: since vs for <> since = Zeitpunkt, for = Zeitdauer
Unterschied: some vs any <> some = positiv, any = negativ/Frage

Passive Voice Bildung => to be + Past Participle
Conditional 1: Struktur => if + Simple Present, will + Infinitiv
Conditional 2: Struktur => if + Simple Past, would + Infinitiv
